<subSubSection id="C6C57ACAFFDDFFE9FF29FDCB40791BB3" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8E602941FFDDFFE9FF29FDCB40791BB3" blockId="3.[158,780,503,1227]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="BCABF553FFDDFFE9FF29FDCB40431B10" bold="true" box="[158,274,599,622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species may be differentiated from other members of the 
<taxonomicName id="49DF52C2FFDDFFE9FEE5FDEA43781BF3" baseAuthorityName="Walch" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[338,553,630,653]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Astraptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgerator">
<emphasis id="BCABF553FFDDFFE9FEE5FDEA43781BF3" box="[338,553,630,653]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Astraptes fulgerator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by the following unique character states of the DNA barcode: 379G; 389C; 391G.
</paragraph>
